    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
                <p><bibl><ptr target="#oliverioDAI2"/>, pp. 116-117, n. <citedRange>115</citedRange>, fig. 71</bibl>, whence 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SEG"/>, <citedRange>9.227</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>027100</citedRange></bibl>.
                    Cf. <bibl><ptr target="#beschi1970"/>, pp. <citedRange>182, 186, 204</citedRange></bibl>; 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#laronde1987"/>, pp. <citedRange>52-58</citedRange></bibl>, whence 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SEG"/>, <citedRange>38.1892</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#belzic2022"/>, catalogue <citedRange>B.5</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-64956"><name nymRef="#Μεγώι">Μεγὼι</name>
                    <lb n="2"/><persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-65032"><name type="patronymic" nymRef="#Μνάσαρχος">Μνασάρχω</name></persName></persName>
	 </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p/>
 </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="fr" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Megô fille de Mnasarkhos.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="en" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Mego daughter of Mnasarchos.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="it" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Megò figlia di Mnasarchos.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="ar">
            <p>ميجو بنة مناسارخوس</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>Mego was a member of a proeminent family, whose monumental tomb is well known.</p>
                <p>Because of its larger dimensions, Beschi was able to suspect that the half-bust placed upon this base was n. 38 of his catalogue.</p>
                <p><bibl><ptr target="#oliverioDAI2"/>, p. <citedRange>116</citedRange></bibl>, footnote 1, explained that he could only give drawings of the bases from
                    Mnasarkhoi tomb and would publish the photographs in a next section, but that never happened.</p>
                <p/>
            </div></body>
    </text>
